headline.print_headline: How the Dow Jones Industrial Average Did Monday
headline.main: How the Dow Jones Industrial Average Did Monday

lead_paragraph: U.S. stock prices moved quietly higher Monday as investors decided to step back into a market that was rattled by turbulence last week. A decline in IBM held back a gain in the Dow Jones industrial average. IBM fell 7 percent after it reported quarterly results that missed analysts' expectations. The company also cut its earnings outlook.
